AUTO-REVIEW (undated) Buick's challenge was daunting: redesign its
very successful full-size LeSabre for a new generation without
alienating the old one. So the LeSabre for 2000 has been revamped
nose to tail without being too blatant about it. Until you take a
closer look, it's easy to mistake the new LeSabre for the 1999
model. All the cues are still there, but they've been smoothed out
and better integrated, not quite modernized but more in touch with
today's styling trends. By BOB GOLFEN. Story will move in the ``L''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
SURVIVOR (Phoenix) - Now, there is only Caroline Kennedy
Schlossberg, the sole survivor of her immediate family, bearing the
deaths of first her father, then her mother and now her brother.
And there is only Douglas Whitneybell. The Phoenix man, too, is the
sole survivor of his immediate family, losing first his father,
then his brother and then his mother. ``The most important thing is
to have a support system around you,'' said Marty Tousley, a
bereavement counselor for Hospice of the Valley, a non-profit
agency that provides care and services for terminally ill people
and their families. By KARINA BLAND. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GORDON (Phoenix) - State Rep. Tom Gordon worked for the Central
Intelligence Agency at one time and received extensive intelligence
training in the Navy, according to sources familiar with Gordon's
background and records obtained Friday by ''The Arizona Republic.''
Congressional sources said Friday that Gordon was fired by the CIA
prior to his stints in the offices of U.S. Sen. John McCain,
R-Ariz., and Rep. J.D. Hayworth, R-Ariz. The details of Gordon's
military history come to light as the FBI investigates whether
Gordon lied his way onto a free flight to Bosnia arranged by
Hayworth. By CHRIS MOESER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
