<P>
   BRAZIL-ARMOR (Sao Paulo, Brazil) _ One morning in March, two men
shot at point-blank range at the driver of a sedan carrying the
three school-age children of Jorge Paulo Lemann, one of Brazil's
wealthiest men. The car was armored, so just one of the 20 bullets
punctured the driver's window, grazing his right arm. He sped to
safety. The company that armored the car, O'Gara-Hess &AMP; Eisenhardt
Armoring Co., based in Fairfield, Ohio, is basking in the media
coverage. O'Gara's sales of armored cars at its Sao Paulo office
tripled, and business is also booming at the 20 or so other
car-armoring companies here. By Simon Romero.
