Street's last large private investment partnerships, appears poised
to try again to sell its stock to the public in an offering that
analysts expect to value the money manager at more than $2 billion.
By Richard A. Oppel Jr.
</P>
<P>
   SUNRISE-PLUNGE (Undated) _ For most of this year, the chat on
the Internet had it that Sunrise Technologies International Inc., a
tiny California medical device company, was a stock sure to deliver
a bountiful return. So far, though, it has served up only
heartburn. By David J. Morrow.
