<HEADLINE>
KREIGER, CROMSIGT WIN AT IRWINDALE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEITH LAIR  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRWINDALE, Calif. _ It was a double pleasure Friday night for
Larry Kreiger and Gerrit Cromsigt.
</P>
<P>
   Racing under Irwindale Speedway's newly formatted schedule, both
drivers won two main events before a crowd of 2,195.
</P>
<P>
   Kreiger won both 25-lap Grand American races and Cromsigt took
both 30-lap Late Model races.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a lot of work, said Grand American points leader
Kreiger, of Thousand Oaks. ``The question is how does two wins
feel, not just one. It's hard to believe. My sponsor told me to
take it easy in the first race and go all out in the second.
</P>
<P>
   Cromsigt, from Pine Mountain Club, replaced an engine and two
tires en route to his 30-lap double victories.
</P>
<P>
   ``Basically, we have Brian Kelley's 100-year-old engine, he
said. ``We had the car set up really well until blowing the engine
last week, so we kept the same set-up. I think we'll run it that
way the rest of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Bernhardt got into the right place at the right time in
the Mini Stock main event.
</P>
<P>
   The Fontana resident was running behind San Bernardino's Tony
Shreve and San Bernardino's Al Edenfield on the eighth lap. Shreve
began throwing oil, causing Edenfield to spin and Bernhardt came
out with the lead and held on to win the 20-lap main event. La
Verne's Scott Porter finished second. ``We had a tight car and a
bit of luck, Bernhardt said.
</P>
<P>
   Cromsigt made up his six-point deficit on Late Model leader
Dusty McDonald, of Simi Valley.
</P>
<P>
   McDonald finished third in the first main and second in the
final main. They are now tied for the series points lead.
</P>
<P>
   Rip Michels of Mission Hills passed Santa Clarita's John
Watkinson for second in the Grand Am points race, but fell six more
points behind Kreiger, who leads by 48 points. Canyon Country's Rod
Johnson finished second in the first main with Michels third and
they reversed the finish in the second main.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-24-99 0238EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
