</P>
<P>
   Former athletic director Paul Bubb and his boss, vice president
Ron Kopita, made the decision two years ago to cut four men's
sports and keep football in order to meet financial and
gender-equity goals. Ultimately, both were forced to resign.
</P>
<P>
   Most athletes and alumni want to see football continue, and Dick
Dull _ the new athletic director _ said the school benefits from it
with improved fund-raising and increased exposure.
</P>
<P>
   ``Like it or not, the public appetite is men's basketball and
football,'' Dull said. ``When you drop one of them, the attention
of the other sports could be affected.''
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
