<HEADER>
A2588 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MAFIA-GANGS-2ndTAKE-L     07-24 0331
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAFIA-GANGS-2ndTAKE-LADN </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES: to talk things out.''
</P>
<P>
   Seban of the LAPD's Foothill Division said the peace treaty is
no longer as formidable a force as it once was.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know we have a lot of gang-related homicides and shootings
here in Foothill, and I don't see any evidence of the peace
treaty.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition to assigning more officers to problem areas, both
Foothill and Devonshire divisions are aggressively working with
their CLEAR (Community Law Enforcement and Recovery) programs that
partner police officers with probation agents, residents and
prosecutors.
</P>
<P>
   The Foothill and Devonshire divisions are where most
gang-related crimes have taken place. They are up 31 percent and 64
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
   The Valley's three other divisions saw decreases in gang-related
crime, including North Hollywood, which had a 32 percent drop
compared to last year.
</P>
<P>
   Devonshire Division officials blame most of their 166 gang
crimes, 65 more than last year, on having recently taken control of
a 1.3-mile area that the Van Nuys Division was responsible for last
year.
</P>
<P>
   Gang-related crime in this area of Panorama City, nicknamed the
Witch's Hat for its triangular shape, was not included in
Devonshire's statistics last year, officials said. And it is one of
the Valley's leading crime hotspots for gang and drug activity.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a heavily populated area with gang and drug activity.
There's more gangs in a smaller area,'' said Devonshire Capt. John
Egan.
</P>
<P>
   Even still, murders in Devonshire were down dramatically, from
10 last year to one this year.
</P>
<P>
   In the Northeast Valley Foothill Division, there were 169
gang-related crimes this year, up from 129 last year.
</P>
<P>
   Murders in Foothill were up from 10 to 15 during the first six
months of this year. Rapes in Devonshire were up from 33 to 41.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the increase in gang-related offenses, overall serious
crime in Foothill was down 21 percent.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
