<DOCNO> NYT19990724.0103 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-24 12:28 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4502 &Cx1f; var-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CLINTON-PROMISES-REVI     07-24 1085
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CLINTON-PROMISES-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
YOU COULD LOOK IT UP: WHAT HE PROMISED. AND WHAT HE DID. 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089) 
(bl) 
 By DAVID E. ROSENBAUM   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ At his news conference last week, President Clinton
was asked why he ridiculed George W. Bush's slogan of
``compassionate conservatism.'' Another questioner wanted to know
what the president found objectionable about the Texas governor's
``trying to present a new moderate face for his party, just like
you did for the Democrats.''
</P>
<P>
   Clinton responded that Bush had not met the responsibility of
presidential candidates to ``make their positions clear on the
