<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Armstrong's next stage: TV show circuit
 &HT;    By Suzanne Halliburton
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   FUTUROSCOPE, France _ After this week, most people in the United
States will have caught a glimpse of Lance Armstrong on national
television.
</P>
<P>
   Armstrong, who is set to win the Tour de France in Paris this
afternoon, is scheduled for a one-day, whirlwind media tour in New
York starting Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   First on the agenda is three days of recuperating and
celebrating his impressive Tour win with his wife and mother at his
European base in Nice, France.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Stapleton, Armstrong's Austin, Texas-based agent, said
Armstrong will fly from France via chartered jet as a guest of Nike
to New York Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   By late Saturday, Armstrong had confirmed appearances on ``Late
Night with David Letterman''; ``Larry King Live''; ``The Today Show
on NBC''; ``CBS This Morning'' and on ``Live with Regis and Kathie
Lee.''
</P>
<P>
   Armstrong also likely will make an appearance on ABC's ``Good
Morning America''.
</P>
<P>
   He will return to Europe for several cycling exhibitions and
then will jet back to his home country, visiting Los Angeles on
Aug. 8 for a likely appearance on the ``Jay Leno Show.'' He then
will be feted by Nike, his longtime sponsor, at a party to
celebrate his victory at Nike headquarters in Beaverton, Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   Armstrong will be in Austin on Aug. 10, where a public
celebration is in the planning stages. Stapleton said a parade and
reception has been mentioned.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
