<P>
   ANIMAL-ALLIES _ WASHINGTON _ Cockroaches wearing backpacks and
elite troops of trained honeybees are among the recruits the
Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency is considering for
possible use in detecting land mines and chemical or biological
warfare agents. DARPA's year-old Controlled Biological Systems
Program is working on ways to use natural creatures or copy some of
their techniques to detect environmental hazards on the
battlefield. (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Eds: MOVED Wednesday. With photos.
