<P>
   ENCRYPTION _ WASHINGTON _ The House is heading for a showdown
over the issue of encryption software for computer data. The
government enforces strict export limits on the software for
national security reasons, but U.S. technology companies are
worried about losing the market to foreign firms who face no such
restrictions. Five different House committees are under orders to
finish their bills by Friday, and so far their approaches differ
widely. (Glass, Cox News Service)
</P>
