</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) GRACKO, Yugoslavia -- July 24, 1999 --
KOSOVO-SERB-DEATHS, 7-24 -- Dostana Stojanovic, the widow of one of
the victims in the worst single attack against the few Serbian
civilians left in Kosovo since NATO troops arrived last month,
being comforted by family members at her home in Gracko. Officals
say that 14 Serbian farmers were killed, some disfigured with blunt
instruments. More than 80,000 of the 200,000 Serbs in Kosovo when
the NATO bombing ended have left since alliance troops arrived in
mid-June. (Tyler Hicks/New York Times Photo)
</P>
