<SLUG> BC-BBN-NLNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RACE IS ON FOR GWYNN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ San Diego is moving in on San Francisco in the
West, which should take some of the pressure off Tony Gwynn's
pursuit of 3,000 hits.
</P>
<P>
   Most hitters believe a pennant race is an easier place to
achieve individual goals than on a dead team 35 games out. Gwynn
enters today's game needing 13 hits to reach 3,000, one more than
Tampa Bay's Wade Boggs. And don't think there isn't competition.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was able to pass him up in lifetime average (.339-.329)
after 1998, and I'm proud of that,'' Gwynn said. ``I'd like to get
to 3,000 first. It's a motivation for me. But I'm pulling for Wade
and Cal (Ripken) to make it, too. To get 3,000 hits shows
consistency.''
</P>
<P>
   Boggs, 41, batted .349 in his first full season with the Red Sox
in 1982. He then won batting titles five of the next six years. His
last title was in 1988.
</P>
<P>
   Gwynn, 39, has eight batting titles, including a .351 average in
his first full year of 1984. &QL; 
Show me the green
</P>
<P>
   Reds All-Star shortstop Barry Larkin, who caused quite a stir in
Cincinnati by saying he wanted to play on grass after his contract
expires after the 2000 season, now says he wants to help make it
happen at home.
</P>
<P>
   Larkin has said he would help pay the $1 million-$1.5 million it
would cost to rip up Cinergy Field's artificial turf and put in the
real stuff.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's not out of the realm of possibility,'' Larkin said.
``If it comes up in my contract negotiations, I'll consider it. I
think it's that important that we have grass.''
</P>
<P>
   Reds general manager Jim Bowden replied: ``We take all cash
donations.'' &QL; 
Beck's back
</P>
<P>
   Cubs reliever Rod Beck was activated Wednesday and though he
returned six weeks ahead of schedule after undergoing elbow
surgery, it probably is too late to help the team.
</P>
<P>
   Beck was reportedly clocked at 92 mph during one of two rehab
stints at Triple-A Iowa. That's more than 10 mph faster than he was
throwing in the wild-card playoff against the Giants last year.
Terry Adams has been doing a good job as the closer lately. For
now, Beck will join his replacement, Rick Aguilera, in pitching
middle relief. &QL; 
Not now
</P>
<P>
   The Phillies chose a bad time to get banged up with
division-leading Atlanta in town this weekend for a four-game
series.
</P>
<P>
   All-Star catcher Mike Lieberthal was sent back to Philadelphia
on Wednesday for an MRI on his aching right elbow. Results were
negative.
</P>
<P>
   After serving as a DH for five straight games in AL ballparks,
right fielder Bobby Abreu is out because of a sore right elbow that
forced him to miss five games in May.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Rolen had to leave Wednesday night's game in the fifth
inning with a strained lower back. Rico Brogna is playing with a
broken toe on his left foot.
</P>
<P>
   To top it off, pitcher Curt Schilling is bothered by biceps
tendinitis that has made it increasingly difficult to get loose. He
lasted only five innings Friday. &QL; 
Game time
</P>
<P>
   Arizona's Randy Johnson starts tonight against the Dodgers'
Kevin Brown after shutting out the Mariners on Tuesday in his
return to Seattle. It was his 25th career shutout and lowered his
league-leading ERA to 2.65. He struck out 10 to increase his career
total to 2,558, passing Jerry Koosman for fifth all-time among
left-handers (18th overall).
</P>
<P>
   ``Randy gave a very Randy-esque performance,'' Seattle's Alex
Rodriguez said Tuesday. ``He really stuck it to us.''
</P>
<P>
   Still hard to believe the victory ended a string of four
consecutive Johnson starts where the Diamondbacks were shut out.
Johnson was the 10th pitcher since 1900 to lose four straight by
shutout.
</P>
<P>
   The worst might have been the Mets' Jim McAndrew in 1968. They
were the first four starts of his career and he had a 1.82 ERA
during that stretch. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
